0 Param data.1 string m_text: Do forgive me, but I'm still preparing the formula. Come back some other time.
I've just wrapped up preparations for my next formula. You have a weapon, yes? Let's see what can be done with it.
I've just perfected a new formula. If you're prepared to pay, I'm prepared to transmute.
Welcome, traveler. If you're off to fight the Oni, you'd best go well armed.
You've brought weapons and shadestones, yes? I can transmute something for you, if you like.
Come on, Kagachi. Let's go.
Father... Mother...
What is it?
You coming with me?
It's nothing.
Yeah.
Oh...
You know about the Watchers? They're so cool! I'm gonna be one someday!
I wanna join the Watchers one day. That's why I keep up my sword practice!
I heard they caught that person from the cult. The Watchers helped get him, right? I just know they did!
Once I join the Watchers my mom won't have to worry about a thing. I'll be strong enough to keep her safe!
Wait, how do you even get to be a Watcher? Is it first come, first served?
What if I don't even get in? I'm not that smart. Maybe I can't be a Watcher.
Seven-Day Sendings are pretty, huh? My dad makes the braziers for them.
Actually, being the brazier maker wouldn't be so bad! Maybe I should ask my dad how he makes them.
Someone nasty's on the loose, but the Watchers will handle it! And I'm gonna see that they do!
I am SO gonna become a Watcher! And then I'll keep my mom safe next time somethin' happens!
I can't let him go out in the middle of all this chaos. How in the Veil did things get so bad?
Unbelievable. Going outside without asking when it's so dangerous. The boy must have a death wish!
He's insistent on becoming a Watcher. Says they're our heroes! All that stubbornness comes from his father.
I've been looking for Big Bro, but I can't find him anywhere.
He promised he'd take me to see the Ark of Hope's secret base, but he overslept again. Figures...
Guess this means they caught the Navigator before we got to go. But there's still the trial, so maybe we'll go anyway.
He's not really my big brother. He's my neighbor. We play all the time, but he's sleeping in again.
I keep talking louder and louder in funny voices, but he just won't wake up. He says deeper sleep makes for better moods.
Big Bro says he'll buy me a charm—so we can be together in the next life, you know? He's a good guy.
His mom's pretty sick. He's out visiting her, so I'm waiting right here for him.
Oh no, this is bad! Really bad! Big Bro's not here yet! How can he still be asleep!?
I knew Big Bro would come through! He came out, told me it was too dangerous, and then let me come inside.
Papa says I'm good with a sword! That's why I wanna be a guard when I grow up!
Papa's a guard. They're so cool-looking!
Did Papa catch the bad cult man? It'd be really cool if he did!
Some people say I can't be a guard. Well, I'll show them!
Papa tells me to watch what I say when we're outside. But why? I don't get it.
Mama's been asking me if I want to change my mind, since it's so dangerous lately.
But I wanna be a guard! Why doesn't Mama get it?
Papa says I can't be a guard because I'm no good with a sword.
But I'm better than everyone around here. Maybe he'll change his mind when I become a guard!
Hey! I'll never talk about becoming a guard again! Just promise you'll help Papa!
We've quelled the uprising, but continued vigilance is key. We have yet to receive word that the ringleader has been captured.
I thought it would help if I dissuaded my daughter from aspiring to become a soldier, but my selfishness helped fuel this mess.
I only wanted to do what was best for her... Clearly I still have much to learn.
Has anyone ever told you you look like Io and Wu?
We're not allowed to go in that pond over there. They say it's sacred...whatever that means.
Oh, hey there! What's all this Ark of Hope business? I keep hearing it, but I don't know what it is.
I've been hearing strange voices... I cover my ears, but it's really scary. Will you keep me safe?
Everyone tells me it's too dangerous to go outside. But I know Wu will keep me safe!
I hear more scary voices all the time, but now that you're here it's okay, right? Right?
Io said something else happened that makes it unsafe to go outside. But nothing happened to me last time!
They keep telling me I should stay inside, but there's nothing to do inside! So here I am.
Besides, nothing's gonna happen to me, 'cause you're out here! Isn't that right?
I love the Seven-Day Sending! It's like the air is dancing with light!
Help me! You can't let Io and Wu die, okay!?
Io and Wu were just here. You saved them, didn't you? Oh, thank you so much!
You need something, or what? Sorry, let me start over. I'm not much of a people person. They say I've got no social graces.
Ah, you again. I'm just out here waiting for my husband. He's tied up with all his guard duties.
I heard they charged the Navigator. It's only right he pays for what he's done.
I used to be a guard too, you know. I heard about the most recent incident through one of my contacts. Tough stuff. Stay strong out there.
My husband got unusually worked up talking about how there aren't as many kids as there used to be.
I hear you caught the killer, but this is far from over. My husband got a fresh set of orders right away.
My husband told me not to leave the house, but waiting for him is what I do. So here I am!
I lost many a friend in my days as a guard. You mustn't grieve, but you mustn't get used to it, either.
At times like these, guards puff out their chests and swear they will be strong. That's what gave me the strength to carry on, anyway.
I'm waiting here for my husband's return. Life without him would be the most boring thing I could possibly imagine.
Sometimes I get impatient. I think about suiting up and heading out to greet him myself, but then I think about how long it'd take to find my equipment.
Looks like the commotion's finally died down.
My husband was off again just as soon as he'd returned. Even that brief little encounter has filled me with life.
Say, you always been that young? Oh, you're not my wife! Pardon me, son.
She's gettin' big, y'know. Gotta look up to catch her eye!
I would've caught the Navigator m'self if I were younger! Used to be a guard, y'see. I'd make him whimper, I would!
Seems there's always a ruckus these days. We never had anything like this when I was growin' up. The world's gone crazy.
The Night Devil...I've heard that name before. But watch who ya say that to. You'll catch some heat from the guards.
Seems like there's more 'n' more of them that'd do harm to us, and the whole kingdom's gone to the dogs. I'd shout 'em down right quick if I were younger.
Watch yourself, son. There's somethin' out there with more of a mind to kill than any ol' monster.
A murderous intent is more dangerous than anything. Sows fear amongst the people, see. Watch your back, son.
Wha—! I'm not one of 'em! I'm a guard, doggonit! I'm here to protect this town!
Things've gotten pretty tough, haven't they dear? Oh, it's you again.
I was a decorated veteran, I'll have you know! I'd get back out there if I weren't past my prime...
Something awful happened on my watch, and I keep training so it won't happen again.
I'll be the one to bring the Night Devil to justice. Mark my words.
Get back! Monsters could reappear at any moment! Where'd they come from?
What is it, little one? If you need directions, ask someone else. I don't know the area too well, myself.
The Executioner... Nothing could possibly justify such senseless murder.
The Blood Guard have been dispatched to the mountains. Perhaps they've finally located the Night Devil.
Tch! Those fools! Slicing down the Fallen is one thing, but killing a man... I'm gonna be sick.
You look rather busy. Why don't you stop and smell the roses?
Relax, it's okay. I mean you no harm. Until recently I was a Watcher, myself.
Ah, some things never change. With that attitude, the petals shall slip from your hands, and so too shall love.
Hitoha, Kujo, Mayura... Wait, did Hitoha have a boyfriend?
You know, I thought the Navigator was up to something, but I never imagined it would become such a problem.
The voices have grown louder of late. I was content to leave them a mystery as a child, but now... They're louder, aren't they? No need to answer.
This flower has lost a petal. Even the most precious of blossoms can wilt so quickly. Just like me.
I think the kingdom's going a bit too far, and I can see you feel the same. I'm with you. I don't think it's good.
Someone has been obsessed with destroying my flowers. Soon enough they will pay for what they've done.
The rites of a Seven-Day Sending bring back such memories and emotions. Knowing you'll be with that special someone again...
With all that's going on, her departure from this world may well be a blessing.
She was as fond of people, peace, and happiness as I am. We must not be passive observers.
I only caught a glimpse of him as he tried to flee, but I can't stop crying...
Isn't that strange? Why is this happening?
Even if disease claims my girlfriend, I'll wait for her. However long it takes. Someday we'll meet again.
I'll do whatever it takes. I know I'll find her in the next life.
Being with her is all I need to be happy. Talking with her is enough to make my heart soar.
Why? WHY!? Why must even death be a struggle!? It isn't right!
Have you heard about the ancient evil that's on the loose? Terrifying, isn't it?
People in the neighborhood start passing away when you get to be my age. No wonder my joints hurt all the time.
I hear there's an evil man they call the Navigator running around. They say he killed a hundred people! How terrible.
Supposedly my friend was wrapped up in that Ark of Hope business. I had a feeling that group was up to no good.
You know I love my gossip, but say too much and the guards will start to take notice. How scary is that?
Oh dear, oh dear... The voices sure are loud these days, aren't they? I can feel them in my bones! This kingdom sure is tough to live in nowadays.
Whoops! That kind of talk is sure to attract the soldiers!  Maybe I should just pick up and move.
I hear women are being targeted. How awful! Thank goodness for the guards, right?
I think the Seven-Day Sending's the only reason I haven't turned my back on the kingdom. It's just so beautiful, every single time.
This is horrible, absolutely horrible! Who did this!? I've never been more terrified!
That's it, I'm moving! There aren't enough souls Beyond the Veil to make living in this place worth it!
I've come to take the last of my belongings, and I can't believe it's so quiet. Is everybody dead? Heh...heh heh!

The hero returns...
His arms break chains.
Are they warm flame or cool blade?
What do you think? I composed it while imagining a Watcher I've yet to meet. With any luck, he'll be a hero!
I'm not composing any poems today. Instead I'm gathering inspiration from this sacred pond. Stillness stirs the creative mind, you see.

The scales have melted, the gavel gone soft.
There are no seats at your funeral.
You asked for this.
I composed this for the Navigator. If you stab someone, you'll get blood on your hands. That's just how it works.

Lies, the ideal ostentation.
Swallowed copper dolls.
Are these voices their dying cries?
I wrote this one about the victims of the Ark of Hope tragedy and the voices we've all been hearing. I hope it will still reach them.

Symbol of light, two-colored candle.
Would I could see you melt
To a beautiful swirl.
This one's for me, actually. There's someone I've long admired, and this is practice for reciting it in front of them!

Voices reach out, now but a whisper.
The shadows grow thick,
poised to snuff out gathered glimmers.
This one's about everything happening lately, and the chorus of voices. I can tell they're scared, so I hope this soothes them.

Where have you gone?
The question breeds confusion.
Who is truly lost?
This has a deeper meaning, but I want you to feel it rather than say it, lest we attract the guards' scorn.

Eyes lock in oath.
Fingers entwine, the promise sealed.
Support, unwavering and strong.
This is about what I'm prepared to do. I'm going to read this when I propose to my love!
Apologies if you've come to hear a poem. My love and I must flee this place.
I don't know the truth behind the tragic attack on the kingdom, but I have me and mine to protect.

Is this eating me, or are we merging?
I cannot leave.
Down, down, down I sink...
Forgive me, I'm bringing down the mood! I'm just working through something personal. Don't mind me.

Farewell, my love.
Farewell, cruel world.
Farewell future...
I'm going to die soon. But now that I've composed a poem about my passing, I feel rather at ease.

Does the seed know it is a branch?
Does the branch know it is a tree?
Does the tree know it will rot?
My death has little bearing on the kingdom at large, but I nonetheless pray that the kingdom remains happy and healthy after I'm gone.

How brilliant!
What a waste to pass in obscurity!
I grow drunk with happiness.
I'm still not great, but I keep honing my poetic craft. It was love at first sight, really. I'll write a poem that will get his attention yet!

There is no shame in being invisible.
Invisibility would pose no hardship.
But being visible brought me to you!
I always end up writing these sorts of poems. I'd like to structure them better, but I just can't help it!

I rub my eyes, two lukewarm waters.
On the west windowsill, sun pouring in.
An intimate dream ascends.
I won't get anywhere with poems like these! I've got to make them better!

My heart aches, that I may split in two.
Day by day it grows stronger.
I fear I shall drown.
The unease within me grows ever stronger. It's a little scary. Oh, listen to me going on and on about him!
There once was a horror they called the Executioner. Everyone was terrified of it. *hic*
The Night Devil's been makin' moves and causin' a ruckus, hasn't it? That's who we used to call the Executioner!
I heard the Ark of Hope got hauled off. And none too soon! They were gettin' to be a nuisance in the plaza.
What's with all these voices? I thought gettin' rid of the Ark of Hope would quiet things down around here. I can't take it!
There aren't many kids around these days, but I don't mind the quiet. 'Course, sayin' that'll bring the guards to my house. What a pain!
This kingdom's become a nightmare to live in! Even idle complaints make the guards harass ya!
I don't like those, whataya call 'em...Seven-Day Sendings.
All this nonsense is starting to mess with my buzz. Time to break out the good stuff!
Some guy all foamin' at the mouth with anger started in on me. What's his problem? Ruined the mood... *hic*
You got a problem!? If you wanna kill me, take your best shot! *urp* W-Wait, time out!
Weee... *hic* There's more dead'n I can count. Friends, lovers... Ah, dangit!
My daughter's just been born! I'd drink, but it seems a shame. I want a clear head for this!
I'm done drinking now that my daughter's here. Watching her grow sounds like a better time anyhow!
Alcohol! Alcohol's the key! At last, I understand! You drink to forget, and I'm gonna forget it all!
Hey, hey, watch it, pal. I'm all out of charms, so get outta here and don't come back.
How many times do I have ta tell ya this is my alley? Get outta here!
The Navigator? Don't know 'im. Don't care to. Do I look like I have that kinda time? Eh?
I'm hearin' things. Can't tell if they're voices or just noise... This somebody's idea of a joke?
This kingdom, I swear. Gotta watch what ya say, what ya do... It's unbelievable. Drives me up the wall.
You on a little alley expedition with those daggers? Eh? Don't make me laugh. Get outta here.
I'm not movin' from this spot! Didn't you hear a woman got kidnapped!? What if somethin' happened to my mother!
Not another step, or you'll regret it! I'll make short work of anyone who comes near my mother!
You gotta help me! My mom's in there! I was tryin' to get her to the Ark when everything went sideways!
I'm beggin' ya! She hasn't done anything wrong! Please help her get onto the Ark!
Would you happen to know where my son went? I do wish he wouldn't run off like this.
Did you just come back from the outside? How was it? What did you see!? Er...sorry, I'm getting too excited.
I want to travel, but the Fallen are everywhere. Too scary for me! I'll just listen to other travelers' stories.
Hey, have you been anywhere lately? The ruins? Why'd you go out there again?
Hang on a second. You hear that? The city's dead quiet, and the air's cold and crisp. I love it!
If I'd known the Ark of Hope's Quay was out in the ruins, I'd have paid a visit before they got arrested. But deserted ruins are too scary for me!
Then again, they wouldn't call them ruins if they weren't deserted, would they. Now I'm just talking in circles...
Where are you off to now? The marshes? Ah yes, I've read all about how mysterious they are.
Moss-covered ground, gentle breezes, water so still it's like a mirror... Argh, I wanna go!
*sigh* At this point, I'm looking for a reason to travel. Any at all. I just need one.
I've got a list of places I've always wanted to go, but it's so dangerous. I just need an excuse.
You went to the ruins? Like, THE ruins? That's so cool! It must be worth the risk to see all that old architecture!
Rumor has it you can walk on water there. Like, looking at the ruins puts you in touch with some ancient power or something. Oh man, that's so cool!
Mt. Teora! Wow. The path up there is pretty rough, so take extra care.
Standing on the mountainside and looking out over everything must be great. You could even pick up an aegis flute while you're there. Nice!
No, no, no! The city's supposed to be safe! If Fallen are going to invade, then we might as well live in the wilds!
Wait—what if this is the excuse I've been looking for? I could get out now and go on an adventure.
That's it, I'm gonna go check out the one place I've always wanted to see! Ooh, I can't wait!
Somewhere out there is a place called the Eternal Garden. Have you heard of it? Apparently its beauty is otherworldly.
I'd love to go see it. It'll probably be the most dangerous journey I've ever taken.
Natural beauty is a massive inspiration to me. I have to go see it for myself.
I returned from my trip to quite the scene! Apparently my wife was worried sick about me.
I think my trip to the Eternal Garden will have to wait a little while longer.
I told my wife this could be the most dangerous trip I've taken yet, but she sent me off the same way she always does.
So I've got to come back in one piece, the same way I always do.
Why do you look so familiar? Have we met before, young man?
Your face brings back a lot of memories. And I mean decades-old memories. Goodness, so much happened back then.
I've got it. You remind me of my husband when he was young. You're a strong, handsome young man just like he was.
And come to think of it, my husband reminded me of someone else. Who was that? Someone important, probably...
I used to be terrified of men, see. Sure, I can talk to them now, but back then it was scary!
I can't remember why I felt so intimidated at the start, but that's probably for the best. No sense remembering fear!
All this unrest we're going through reminds me of painful things from the past, too. I don't know what I'll do if history repeats itself...
There was a rebellion here, a long time ago. It was awful. People took advantage of the commotion and did terrible things.
Thinking back, that was probably what put the fear of men in me. Sorry for going to such a dark place, dear.
I'm glad they caught that kidnapper. I pray his victims can pass Beyond the Veil in peace.
Tragedy is going to strike again, isn't it. And people like me will suffer.
I never thought I'd see such horror again in my lifetime. I hope everyone is okay.
Gyah! I'm so sorry! I just get so f-flustered around men. P-Please forgive me!
Oh, no! My apologies! I'm just not comfortable around men. I'm getting better, though!
Well hi there! See? I'm much better at small talk now! Perhaps TOO good, hehe...
Eep! Y-You'll have to excuse me. Sorry, I... Sorry.
Oh, pardon me. I'd appreciate it if you could stay and talk for a moment. Er, but don't feel obligated!
Ahem! It's, ah... It's rather nice weather we're having! Phew... Small talk is hard.
Eep! Pardon me! I'm so sor—oh. It's just you.
That's such a relief. Which is strange, because you're still you. A man, that is.
You look pretty tough. Mentally, I mean. Eyes forward. You've got purpose.
My dad would've liked you. He always told me staying mentally tough was the key.
I just got a nice bit of work done, so I'm taking a break. Gotta take care of the kids and all.
The Ark of Hope, eh? They're the ones who were recruiting folks just off that way, right? Guess they were dangerous after all.
I hear there were kids among the Ark's victims. I can't bear to think about our kids getting mixed up in that.
Can't believe there was another incident—not that the kids care. This is why I have to watch over 'em.
People 'round here are letting slip that they're a bit worried about the next life. No one dares say that too loud, though.
I just hope none of this craziness affects the kids.
Things are getting bad, aren't they? Don't worry, we'll take care of the kids. That's our job.
You're a Watcher, aren't you? Look, don't worry about us. We've moved most of the children to safety already. Go help someone else!
Some of the kids still want to go outside, even at times like these. Someone has to watch them; it's too dangerous otherwise.
I don't mind dying. I'll do something just as great in the next life.
Thank goodness the kids and my girlfriend are safe. I like it when things get back to normal.
I like the look of you, kid. I knew a guy who looked like you once.
You've got an intriguing look about you. Strong. But that's not what I'm aiming for.
I'll have a child of my own soon. Perhaps one that's physically weak. But physical strength isn't important.
It's all about the spirit. I'd like to raise my kid to be strong-willed; capable of protecting people.
It's no coincidence that our son was born today.
I'll teach him how to look out for others. How to share what he has with others. And then I'll teach him how to overcome life's disappointments.
I hope my son turns out like you did. Not that I want him to lose his innocence.
What's going on? What should we believe in? The only thing I can trust is what I see with my own eyes.
True strength comes from facing despair only to rise above it. I can tell that strength lies within you.
Do be careful; the children tend to play around here. We wouldn't want anyone getting hurt.
Keep one eye on that blade at your hip. The children can be mischievous.
I understand there were children among the victims. And to think they were recruiting people right under our noses. Dreadful. Just dreadful.
That man right there watches over the children. He's absolutely wonderful.
Apparently he learned everything he knows from his father. What an absolute treasure!
Plenty of people care about children, sure, but rare is the person who looks after those who are not his own.
All of his spare time goes into watching the children. He's an absolute saint.
It's been a bit too dangerous of late to let the children play outside.
A kidnapping, you say? That's disturbing, but I'm not worried. Our wonderful guardian would surely help us, should the need arise.
Looking after these kids makes me want one of my own someday. Perhaps with a certain special someone I've been dreaming of...
We've moved the children to safety. Protect them however you can.
We keep telling him to come inside now that the children have been moved to safety, but he won't hear it.
He keeps insisting there could be more children in need of help, but we want him to look out for himself, as well.
He stood out there the entire time, in the end. I can't tell if he's brave or stupid.
Criminals, Fallen...it all comes 'n' goes. Hang on, Mama, I'm gonna ease your sufferin'!
Heard they arrested that cult leader. Gotta start somewhere, right?
Someone told me all the charges they're throwin' at that cult leader. What kinda scam was he runnin', anyway?
Mama's hearin' strange sounds, and it's drivin' her nuts. So I gotta keep workin' to make life easy for her.
Security's 'bout to get tighter 'round here. Guess it makes sense; there've been a lot of problems lately. Better safe than sorry!
I knew all sorts of people could become Watchers, but I never thought any of 'em would be capable of somethin' like this.
The whole town's on high alert. It's been one crisis after another.
I'm happy to have the work, but obviously I'd prefer a little peace and quiet.
What in the Veil is that bastard Kushi up to now!? I don't think I can stop him.
Listen, find a way to stop Kushi, would ya? I'm gonna round up Mama and help with the kids.
I'm headin' back to my post once this is over. Watch yourself, there're plenty of crazies out there.
Some of 'em are causin' trouble 'cause they don't trust the sovereign.
I'm just glad Mama 'n' I were able to protect the little ones from those crazies, if nothin' else.
My husband doesn't know his own limits. He's not as young as he used to be. *sigh*
Things have been quite hectic for him recently. He really ought to take a break.
I wonder if our boy will want to be a soldier when he grows up. I sure hope he doesn't...
Have you been hearing those strange noises, too? Our poor boy can hardly sleep. He's only just now drifted off.
It's been quite dangerous lately, hasn't it.
We've forbidden our boy from going outside. I feel terrible keeping him all cooped up.
Those strange sounds are getting louder and louder. It's all I can do to get our boy to sleep now.
What with all the crimes against women these days, I can't even fetch water from the well without fearing for my life. These are truly dangerous times.
Things have been horrid lately. I don't dare say this in front of my husband, but the sovereign's actions of late worry me.
We're waiting for things to calm down a bit. Fleeing is dangerous as it is, and we have a child to protect.
I do wish my husband were around at times like these, but I'm sure he's running all over town right now.
The moment my husband showed up, I fell in love with him all over again. He's always there when I need him most!
I've put out the fire and told my son-in-law where to change the wee one's diaper. That's enough, right? Still, I worry.
He doesn't know the first thing about caring for a child, you see. But one day he'll... Who am I kidding? This is an accident waiting to happen.
I'm glad they arrested that cult leader before he could brainwash our grandchild.
I think they should've arrested everyone in the whole Ark! What if they just choose a new leader?
What are my daughter and her husband thinking, taking my grandchild out at night!? What if they get kidnapped!?
They say I'm overprotective. Have you ever heard anything so absurd? How can you over-protect something? It's impossible!
First there was that kerfuffle, and now there's been a kidnapping! What's that no-good sovereign doing during all of this!? Honestly!
Where are the soldiers? What if something happens to my grandchild!? Would they take responsibility? Well? Would they!?
I have to do something, for my grandchild's sake.
My mother-in-law hasn't come home. She fled the house in quite a state.
I've taken my wife and son to safety, but I'm worried about her. I hope she's safe.
Greetings, Watcher. I pray you'll be successful today.
Forgive me, Watcher. Have I said something untoward?
Someone I met the other day said I can be careless with my words. Do you think that's so?
I was once attacked by the Fallen, you know. A Watcher saved me.
That was years ago. I never saw that Watcher again... It would be nice to thank him.
Forgive me, but I should like to know more about the Watcher who saved me.
Perhaps a description of him will help you recall him. He was large, powerful, and quite good-looking.
Mother tells me I mustn't go out of doors. I believe she's being overprotective, but there have been a number of troubling incidents recently.
Have you heard about the kidnapping? My mother is so worried, she says I cannot leave the house.
Be that as it may, I have shopping to do.
I overheard someone say something about the Ark of Hope earlier.
I caught a glimpse of who was speaking, and couldn't help but think he looked like the Watcher who saved me all those years ago.
I'm worried about my mother. She flew out of the house in quite a state, and hasn't returned.
I, too, shall pray that those who have passed Beyond the Veil find happiness in the next life.
What's your deal? You think it's weird that I look after the kids, or what?
I don't care about 'em one way or the other, but my grandma went 'n' got all emotionally attached.
Hey, you! One of the little brats ran off. You seen 'im?
We got a lotta kids with too much energy. Grandma's gettin' too old to keep up with 'em.
Great. The kids heard about the cult leader, and now they're goin' crazier than usual.
Watchin' after these kids is the worst. But grandma wants me to, 'n' I can't say no to 'er.
Kids're tougher than you'd think. Hardly any of 'em are bothered by the weird voices.
Grandma keeps sayin' there're fewer kids than there used to be, but we can hardly look after this lot as it is!
Grandma loves a good Seven-Day Sending. Not that I don't, of course.
What is this kingdom comin' to!? Can't they see I've got a grandma 'n' a buncha kids here!? This is insane!
It wasn't just one or two idiots—it was a bunch of 'em! I can't let any of the kiddos out, either! Sheesh!
Handlin' my grandma 'n' the kids is gettin' to be too much. We've got kids who've lost parents, too.
